==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*aig-, *aih-'', from Indo-European ''*eik-'' ‘possession, ability’.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''[[aga|āga]]'', Old Saxon ''[[egan|ēgan]]'', Old High German ''[[eigan]]'', Old Norse ''[[eiga]]'' (Swedish ''[[äga]]''), Gothic *[[𐌰𐌹𐌲𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root is also the source of Avestan ''aēšā-'' ‘ability, possessions’, Tocharian B ''aik-'' ‘to know’.

